cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SC 

This paper deals with the theory of rewriting and narrowing for constructor-based term rewrite systems with call-time choice semantics. It is likely to be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as it develops a thorough theory for let-rewriting, a reduction notion close to classical term rewriting. It is also likely to be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it discusses the semantics of functional logic languages and their rewrite systems. Additionally, it may be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it addresses issues related to specification and programming. The paper also mentions CRWL, a well-known semantic framework, which may classify it under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) as it deals with term graph rewriting.
